a.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Krela</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/31/01 4:52:38 am)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: 58+ Solo</span><hr size=1> I do brownies at 56 with no fancy staffs or epics <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :evil --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/devil.gif ALT=":evil"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Takes 3 bubbles of mana on a good fight and leaves me at a little over half health usually using just steelskin, sod spending 11pp per pull, although I have the luxury of having a 56+ cleric too so dieing isn't so much of an issue.<br>
<br>
I always get single pulls pulling from zone wall using tflux staff, just dont use shackle to pull if both are up, you *will* get both and that hurts. Otherwise, once split I open with IC then shackle and draught (any draught will do, at 56 I only have jiva and flames and I use flames to take advantage of the lower FR due to tflux). Also make sure to pull them a good way away from the brownie camp, otherwise all their friends will start healing your mob too, and you will quickly find yourself going oom.<br>
<br>
Draughts *don't* interrupt their casting, and with 145FR I get hit by their fire nukes for anything between 40 and 220 and have *never* resisted a *single* one, so be prepared and abort early if it goes wrong. Keep MR above 75 or so to resist their grasping embrace spell too, a rooted wizard is a dead wizard.<br>
<br>
Personally I med by the zone wall rather than on the hill in front of the brownie camp, I've been hammered one to many times by equestrielle to do that anymore. Choice is yours.<br>
<br>
Persephonne Cometbringer<br>
Evoker of the Nameless. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uryll.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ryll</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(9/3/01 6:19:56 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: 58+ Solo</span><hr size=1> I have had no problem since 56 single pulling the Brownies. Just open with staff, or anything other then shackles. After the spawn is broke, I always open with Shackles - Staff - Draught - Staff - Draught - and so on. Unless I get resisted or too many fizzles they only get their DOT, root (which I have always resisted so far) and their healing. Their DD seems to take too long to get off, so my Draught interupts them.<br>
<br>
I use Draught of Jiva because it *does* interrupt their casting (when they get close enough to me to see their casting, I see them interupted with every Jiva). I was using Draught of Frost for the better damage, but still always used 7 Draughts and almost always lost my manaskin. With Draught of Jiva, I generally kill between 3 and 5 Brownies per Manaskin, and since they drop 2 to 5 PP per kill, I end up making enough to pay for my rations and peridots. I stopped using Manasink, as I never noticed it making any difference in the end. <br>
<br>
Brownies are boring, but they get me a blue bubble every 3 hours or so, and allow me to watch TV, and do house work/laundry - which I have to do anyway - so all in all, I like it.<br>
<br>
For those that are quading FG elites... Which zone are you doing this in? I know of the 2 in EW, but do not know off-hand where I can find 4 in a kite-able area.<br>
<br>
Thanks,<br>
<br>
Ryll Umbra<br>
59 Wizard (2 yellow from 60! woohoo)<br>
Exiled Legion<br>
Rodcet Nife<br>
